docs.abstract: The drop in the second quarter was the first in 12 years of streaming. And while the company added 2.7 million customers worldwide, Wall Street had expected five million.
docs.snippet: The drop in the second quarter was the first in 12 years of streaming. And while the company added 2.7 million customers worldwide, Wall Street had expected five million.
docs.lead_paragraph: Netflix, the streaming juggernaut that has upended the entertainment industry, showed signs of vulnerability Wednesday when it reported that it had lost 126,000 paid subscribers in the United States during the second quarter. It was the first time the company had shed domestic streaming customers since it started its digital service 12 years ago and its shares fell sharply.

headline.main: Netflix Stock Tumbles as U.S. Subscribers Decrease After Price Increases
headline.print_headline: Netflix Loses Subscribers As Its Rates Get Steeper
